    
    You can ping and redirect stdout to a file:
        ping google.com > ping.log &

    If you would like to redirect stdout and stderror to a file :
        ping google.com &> ping.log &

    You could check the jobs running in the background:
        jobs

    Use the fg and the corresponding job number to bring task bask into the foreground
        fg 1

    * If using zsh, you must use this format: fg %1 

    CTRL+Z can be use to suspend a process
    CTRL+C to end the process
